div1.p:
Did she live there when the prisoner was taken up? - No. She was gone seven months before that;
Richard Harper
often gave her money to pay for things she bought of me.

Do you know who brought this mare first to work with you? - I cannot say that;
James Lawford
was the man who drove the team and first gave me an account of it. Robinson and his son saw the mare in my stable and told me at the Crown that it was not their mare; it went out to water on Wednesday morning and then they both said they knew the mare, and would prove that it was their property.
